I got this game on release in october 2020;
I rage quit around february 2021.
Now I returned to it with a fresh mind and was able to beat it.

I feel it suffers a bit from being too random; Which perks you get to choose can make or break a run;
Sometimes you explore a whole area without finding any useful equipment or health +.

Still, I put 52 hours into it which I enjoyed.

Honestly, this game is amazing.

- Wands, spells, perks and the environment make you actually think about how you want to adjust your build;
- Permadeath means that you'll be replaying it over and over again;
- The difficulty is just hard enough for you to make mistakes constantly, but not give up;
- There are plenty secrets and side paths to explore;
- Coming up with cool wands just feels great!
